Ask in restaurants where their prawn is from if you’re curious. I’m not saying Imported prawns are bad but rather have had more incidents reported on them. Most are okay but Nephrops (Dub Bay Prawn) far better texture and taste. Therefore they command high export prices

A lot of food substitution (fraud) goes on in this international prawn trade. A lot of investigative journalism has been done on it and that’s why food investigative journalism is so important. Some were farmed in very poor water quality and also gel injected

Ask for Nephrops at fishmongers (nephrops norvegicus - Irish-landed prawns, Dublin Bay Prawns) fished in North Atlantic by Irish boats. I’ve been on these boats. Soft texture. Tiger prawns are the Penaeus monodon; several types of these. Lot of Pleoticus from Argentina sold here https://t.co/7dTm0wL0sr
